                    <p>Physicians</p>
                    <p>Utilization Management</p>
                        <h3><a href="#">Guideline Objective(s)</a></h3>
                    <p><div class="content_para"><p>To evaluate the appropriateness of radiologic and other procedures for the follow-up of patients after treatment for Hodgkin lymphoma</p></div></p>
                        <h3><a href="#">Target Population</a></h3>
                    <p><div class="content_para"><p>Patients with Hodgkin lymphoma who have completed their treatment and response assessment</p></div></p>
                        <h3><a href="#">Interventions and Practices Considered</a></h3>
                    <p><ol style="list-style-type: decimal;">
    <li>History and physical examination </li>
    <li>X-ray chest </li>
    <li>Computed tomography (CT)
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;">
        <li>Chest, abdomen, and pelvis </li>
        <li>Neck, chest, abdomen, and pelvis </li>
        <li>Chest </li>
    </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Fluorine-18-2-fluoro-2-deoxy-D-glucose positron emission tomography (FDG-PET)/CT
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;">
        <li>Whole body </li>
        <li>Chest, abdomen, and pelvis (if whole body scan is negative at 6 months) </li>
    </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Mammography </li>
    <li>Magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) breast </li>
    <li>Exercise tolerance test and echocardiogram </li>
    <li>Laboratory tests
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;">
